Unknown.

This species occurs sympatrically with 

A. depressicornis

, but this new species differs from it by having the mandible with weakly developed subbasal and subapical teeth (subbasal and subapical teeth large in 

A. depressicornis

), the digitus posteriorly expanded (digitus slender in 

A. depressicornis

), and the paracuspis tuberculate (paracuspis absent in 

A. depressicornis

).
